@I@ Forty weeks, then forty-two. Then the days played peekaboo. By Wednesday noon, hours kicked, and at forty-three, minutes scratched. We got a pamphlet; doctor withdrew us four as if to reassure.
Induced, the labour is said to be. Post-term, the baby is said to be. Late, the mother is said to be.
Westminster Bridge and its amber lights hazing my tears. For quick respite, wind freezes them in place. As though I need to exhibit such freedoms.

@I@ &lsquo;Who am I?&rsquo; you asked casually. They swept away the philosophy, Called it a flagrant waste of time. You paused and realised the irony. @II@ Misunderstanding is ubiquitous but Understood. Tell me, tell me. Tell me what I am, Who I am and How I am. Because You do it anyway.
Tell me where I am: Perplexed miens of perceived ineptness Or inherited doubt. rid, rid, riddance.
Life&rsquo;s a game, but not for us.
